    "body": "Thanks for reporting this @sshmaxime!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThe problem seems to be that a wasm compiler is being downloaded, but hardhat tries to use it as if it was a native compiler. Apparently, the [solc list for linux](https://binaries.soliditylang.org/linux-amd64/list.json) starts at 0.4.10, so it shouldn't even try to download a native compiler for this version.\r\n\r\nNotice that 0.4.10 doesn't work either, because the `--standard-json` option doesn't work. 0.4.11 seems to work fine.\r\n\r\n@alcuadrado is this something we want to support, even if it's a low priority? Or should we detect that the user is trying to use something older than (say) 0.4.11 and show an error?",
